- No inline `as unknown` casts remain in outbound/stream delivery code
- Both `stream-api.ts` files have proper TSDoc module comments
- New unit tests pass for both wrappers
- All existing adapter tests pass without modification

Refactor `packages/relay/src/adapters/webhook/webhook-adapter.ts` to extend `BaseRelayAdapter` instead of implementing `RelayAdapter` directly, eliminating ~80 lines of duplicated status tracking code.

## Implementation Steps

1. **Read `packages/relay/src/adapters/webhook/webhook-adapter.ts`** to understand the current implementation — it manually tracks status, implements start/stop idempotency, and has its own `setLogger()` method.

2. **Refactor to extend `BaseRelayAdapter`**:

```typescript
import { BaseRelayAdapter } from '../../base-adapter.js';
import type { RelayPublisher, AdapterContext, DeliveryResult } from '../../types.js';
import type { RelayEnvelope } from '@dorkos/shared/relay-schemas';
import type { WebhookAdapterConfig } from '../../types.js';

const NONCE_PRUNE_INTERVAL_MS = 60_000; // or whatever the current value is

export class WebhookAdapter extends BaseRelayAdapter {
  private readonly config: WebhookAdapterConfig;
  private readonly nonceMap = new Map<string, number>();
  private nonceInterval: ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null = null;

  constructor(id: string, config: WebhookAdapterConfig, displayName?: string) {
    super(id, config.inbound.subject, displayName ?? `Webhook (${id})`);
    this.config = config;
  }

  protected async _start(relay: RelayPublisher): Promise<void> {
    // Nonce pruning interval (relay ref already stored by BaseRelayAdapter.start())
    this.nonceInterval = setInterval(() => {
      this.pruneExpiredNonces();
